			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">The proposed project aims at a theoretical and numerical study of time series analysis and change-point detection algorithms based on the use of Singular Spectrum Analysis (SSA), the technique of principal component expansions of time series. The study is based on the use of the extreme value theory for Gaussian random processes, dynamical modelling of population dynamics based on Markov models and Volterra differential equations, Bayes and Markov Chain Monte-carlo methods, aswell as on a numerical analysis of a large number of population and market research dynamics data. At least two articles, one on the theory and another one of applied charater, should be submitted to statistical journals.A software realising time time series analysis and change-point detection algorithms, based on the use of SSA, should be developed and put to INTERNET for a general use.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
